        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the biscuit dough",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Beat the butter and icing sugar until pale. Beat in the egg yolk. Mix in the flour, ground hazelnuts, and salt until the dough just comes together. Flatten into a disc, wrap, and refrigerate for 30 minutes.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the praline",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Line a baking tray with baking paper. Heat the sugar in a dry heavy pan over medium heat without stirring until it melts to a deep amber caramel. Remove from heat and stir in the toasted hazelnuts. Pour onto the lined tray and spread flat. Allow to set hard, about 20 minutes. Break into pieces and blend in a food processor, scraping down the sides, until a smooth paste forms. Beat the praline paste with the softened butter until smooth and spreadable.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Roll, bake, and fill",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Preheat the oven to 170°C conventional. Roll the chilled dough to 4 mm thick on a lightly floured surface. Cut into rounds with a 6 cm cutter. Re-roll the trimmings once only. Bake on lined trays for 10 to 12 minutes until pale gold. Transfer to a rack and cool completely. Spread a generous teaspoon of praline cream on the flat side of half the biscuits and sandwich with the remaining halves, pressing gently.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
